in about an hour.

00:05.596 --> 00:07.564
I gotta say, givin'
away all those clothes

00:07.630 --> 00:09.064
was pretty generous of you.

00:09.130 --> 00:11.397
I figured "Hey, why shouldn't
the less fortunate

00:11.464 --> 00:13.730
be as chic as I was
two years ago.

00:15.464 --> 00:17.697
You're just too good
for this world.

00:17.764 --> 00:19.697
Well, any world actually.

00:21.997 --> 00:23.364
Hey, people.

00:23.430 --> 00:25.397
‐ That coat!
‐ Isn't it sharp?

00:25.464 --> 00:29.464
I found it in a box
on the stoop.

00:29.530 --> 00:32.564
No, Max. This is my coat.
I'm givin' it to charity.

00:32.630 --> 00:35.130
Well, charity
begins at home.

00:35.197 --> 00:37.697
And since I'm in your home,
thank you.

00:40.430 --> 00:42.697
No, you can't have it.

00:42.764 --> 00:46.197
Yeah? Well, said coat was found
outside in an unmarked box.

00:46.264 --> 00:49.097
Proving that possession was
abandoned by its previous owner

00:49.164 --> 00:54.364
or in layman terms,
finders keepers, losers weepers.

00:54.430 --> 00:56.364
I want my coat back.

00:56.430 --> 00:58.930
You don't have the right
accessories to go with it.

00:58.997 --> 01:02.804
Oh! Since I found me a $20 in
this pocket, I can be me some.

01:02.870 --> 01:05.704
Ah‐ah! That‐that's mine.
Max, that's mine.

